Planned models:
    - CNN: baseline
        - Local feature extraction with minimal depth (conv -> relu -> pool -> linear)
        - No sohphistication
    - ResNet-18: residual learning
        - Learn residuals instead of full transformations
        - Skip connections
        - Enables deeper networks
    - DenseNet-121: feature reuse
        - Every layer sees all previous features
        - Concatenation instead of addition (each layer gets [x0, x1, x2,...] instead of x0 -> x1 -> x2...)
        - Improve learning with information sharing
    - EfficientNet-B0: scaling
        - Balance depth, width, and resolution
        - Use compound scaling
        - Optimization of architecture design
    - MobileNetV2: efficiency
        - Separate spatial and channel computation
        - Depthwise separable convolutions
    - ShuffleNetV2: lightweight/channel shuffling
        - Split -> process -> shuffle -> merge
        - Information flow across channels
    - SqueezeNet: fire modules (squeeze + expand layers)
        - Minimize params aggressively
        - Extreme efficiency baseline